 About Ferox 


	The Firm is a discretionary investment manager specializing in the convertibles market. Founded by Jeremy Herrmann, Alexander Warren and Rupert Mathews in February 2000 (as Ferox Capital Management Ltd) and based in London, the Firm now employs 25 people. The Firm was established as we recognized there was a clear business opportunity in delivering superior returns from convertible bonds. Today we manage around $1.7bn of assets across three different core strategies and believe we have substantial capacity to grow this asset base.




